    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">From Mr. C. Darwin, Down, Beckenham</hi></placeName>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>See ‘Nature’ p. 382 about the microphone &amp; earthquakes &amp; tremblings in Japan.—<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
<p>C. D. <lb resp="#mjhawkins"/></p>
<p rend="left">21<hi rend="superscript">st</hi>—</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">0.1 <hi rend="print">Mr</hi>.] <hi rend="italic">altered from </hi>‘<hi rend="print">Mrs</hi>.’ </note>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        
        <div type="footnotes">          
            <note xml:id="foot.f1"><hi rend="italic">Nature</hi>, 19 February 1880, pp. 382–3, reported on a method for detecting seismic trembling in Japan through the use of microphones buried in pits; the method was described by its inventor, <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_8723.xml">John Milne</ref>, a professor of mining and geology at the Imperial College of Engineering, Tokyo.</note>
        </div>
    
    </body>
